'''Linda''' can refer to:
==Middle-earth==
* The [[Quenya]] word ''[[linda]]'' meaning "fair".
* The element ''[[lind]]'', related with "music" both in Quenya and [[Sindarin]] (not to be confused with ''[[lin]]'').
* One of the ''[[Lindar]]'', the name the [[Teleri]] used for themselves.
* [[Linda Proudfoot]] ({{SR|1262}} - {{SR|1363}}), aunt of [[Bilbo Baggins]].
* [[Lindo]], the wise keeper of the [[Cottage of Lost Play]].
==Real World==
* [[Linda Garland]], the wife of artist [[Roger Garland]] and an artist herself.
* [[Linda Greenwood]], author.
* [[Linda Wilson]], author.
